# THE BIGGEST DISAGREEMENT

- The Bull agents (confidence 4/5) believe hyperscaler AI spending is accelerating indefinitely; the Bear agents (confidence 4/5) argue the easy money has been made and growth is normalizing.
- The Meta-Agent (the system's tie-breaker) sided with the Pragmatist's data-quality concern: there simply isn't enough volume or trend history to support the Bull's high confidence, so all decisions were downgraded to 2–3/5 confidence.
- The Contrarian's blind-spot finding was decisive: **nobody has demanded proof that AVGO's custom silicon business is real, or that NVDA's role as the "demand signal" for the entire chain is still valid.** If hyperscalers are building their own chips, NVIDIA becomes less central — and that assumption is unexamined.

